comments.body: File sets needing preservation as of 8/3/23: 81884

Kicking off another round of preservation:

```ruby
parent_resources.each do |resource|
  health_report = HealthReport::CloudFixityCheck.for(resource)
  PreserveResourceJob.set(queue: :super_low).perform_later(id: resource.id.to_s, force_preservation: true) if health_report.valid? && health_report.status == :in_progress
end
```

Create Weekly Slips by LC call number Jobs Task

comments.body:
Heard back from Bobray, generally positive, although interested in excluding:
- Works published by OECD (we have automatic access to all of these works) (#588)
- Works where we already own a work with the same ISBN (de-duplication)
  - This might need to be "future work", since checking against Alma is not currently something this job does. 
  - It might be possible to do this on the WorldShare report side by excluding our own holdings.

Heard back from Jeremy, also generally positive. Requests included:
- Number of holding libraries ("useful but not critical") (#589)
- The text of the title field in native characters, not just Romanized text, since translators don't tend to work on Romanized text (#590)
- All books in the J etc. classes, but only include if they have both the keyword "political" AND are in call numbers D, F, G, H, K or U. Bobray wants books in any class that include his keywords. (#591)
Code has been merged, deployed, and is working, feedback has been ticketed.
